Equality
== vs ===

    == compares values after doing data conversion

    "32" == 32
    goes to true because it converts format to match
    befor comparing the values. *smart* compare - would be a super
    useful thing in spreadsheets lmao

    "32" === 32
    does not do any conversions

    primitives only looking at the value, but objects look at 
    the item in memory - compares same memory pointer?


